                            <comment id="47281" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 03:42:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this test is put into ALWAYS_EXCEPT in bz5494, and I tested it under master and b2_1, both passed locally,&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll try to create a patch to remove it from A_E, and check whether it pass or not in Toro.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47274" author="pjones" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:48:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah sorry - I did not realize that. In that case I will defer to Hongchao to comment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47273" author="jaylan" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:41:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Peter, a new test case recovery-small 24b was created to test this issue as part of the patch. That was how I discovered that test_24&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ab&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; were skipped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know if you want to fix that in this case, since recovery-small.sh is modified anyway, or you want me to open a new case. I am fine either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47272" author="pjones" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 19:33:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jay that is really a separate issue and should be tracked as such. Could you please open a separate ticket to track the issue about test 24? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
